Subject: Re: [T2] Broken Fuel Injector Bolt

On Tue, 19 Jul 2005, Charles Lucas wrote:

> So, I'm changing the rings and hose on my fuel injectors. ('76 westy,
> 2.0L non-Cali) Finished up the last injector, put it back in the hole,
> line up the ring, put the nut on, tighten it down....  and the bolt pops
> out of its hole.  Hmmm...
>
> Now, I'm not sure if the bolt sheared off, or if the hole is stripped.
> The bolt only turns for a couple threads, but that's not enough to hold
> it in place when I tighted down the nut.  Either way I figure I'm in for
> it, 'cause I'm probably going to have to replace the manifold tubes.
>
> Does anyone have a spare one of these injector bolts, and can tell me
> how long it's supposed to be?

thier not all that big, since they are rarely messed with and don't have
to be torqued to 5,000ftlbs I would try something like J-B Weld on it, let
it sit a while then try it again tightening it down very gently to correct
torque.
>
> Also, it looks like a tight fit getting to the bolts that hold on the
> manifold tubes.  Is it even possible to take those off without dropping
> the engine?

yes they will come out, lots of wiggling and contortions


